<item>
            <title>[JCRVLT-162] package installation should not fully open the package when retrieving the package id</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCRVLT-162</link>
                <project id="12314920" key="JCRVLT">Jackrabbit FileVault</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;with the introduction of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCRVLT-113&quot; title=&quot;Skip installation of sub packages if newer version is already present and installed&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JCRVLT-113&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;JCRVLT-113&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCRVLT-114&quot; title=&quot;Subpackage extraction that contains vlt:definitiion might already have installed state&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JCRVLT-114&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;JCRVLT-114&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, the subpackage installation checks if a package is already installed. for that it needs to find existing packages and read their packageid.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the problem is that reading the packageid, even for installed package, needs to open the zip file, and if too big, it&apos;s stream to /tmp. which can cause extensive /tmp and I/O usage during installation of &quot;complex&quot; packages.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
